HEADWORD: Semblable
<hw>Sem"bla*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F., from
<ets>sembler</ets> to seem, resemble, L. <ets>similare</ets>,
<ets>simulare</ets>. See <er>Simulate</er>.]</ety> <def>Like; similar;
resembling.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Semblable</ent>⟦br⟧

